result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Conflict Review Worksheet - No Conflict found

Cases 16CM51 and 15CM355 called together at 3:25pm
Defendant Lincoln R Keeser in court with Attorney Steven John Luchsinger.  ADA Jeffrey Martin Shock appears for the State of Wisconsin.
ADA Shock verifies victim rights compliance 

As to Case 16CM51(Initial Appearance occurs):
Parties agree that the Court does not need to make a record regarding conflict; conflict review record in 15CM355 applies to case 16CM51 as well
The Court finds probable cause to exist in Case 16CM51

As to Both Cases (plea and sentencing occurs):

Maximum penalties recited; Constitutional rights reviewed; plea of " NO CONTEST  " entered on Case 15CM355; factual basis stipulated; the Court accepts the plea, finds Defendant guilty, and orders Judgment of Conviction entered.

On Motion of the State and Joint Recommendation of the Parties, the Court reads-in and dismisses Case 16CM51
Sentencing arguments given by Counsel
Statement made by Mr. Keeser

On Case 15CM355, the Court withholds sentence, and places Defendant on Probation for 1 year, with conditions:
--no acts or threats of violence
--to undergo any assessment, treatment or counseling as deemed appropriate by the Agent
--to submit a DNA sample upon demand
--to pay statutory court costs
--to pay court appointed attorney fees
--Mr. Keeser is to comply with the injunction as it exists

Days credit for time already served:  0  days

The Court directs Mr. Keeser to report to the Probation Office tomorrow.

The Court addresses missed payment of attorney fees with Mr. Keeser, the Court makes paying court appointed attorney fees a condition of Probation, the Court suspends any previous payment order regarding attorney fees.
